  "prompt": "What are some ways you can get into Johns Hopkins University?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to get into Johns Hopkins University:\n\n1. Academic Excellence\n- Maintain a high GPA (typically 3.9+ unweighted)\n- Take rigorous AP, IB, or honors courses\n- Score very high on SAT/ACT (1500+ SAT, 34+ ACT)\n\n2. Strong Application Components\n- Write compelling personal essays\n- Get outstanding letters of recommendation\n- Demonstrate leadership in extracurricular activities\n- Show passion and commitment to specific interests\n\n3. Admission Paths\n- Early Decision (binding application)\n- Regular Decision\n- Transfer student admission\n- Special talent/merit scholarships\n\n4. Academic Strengths\n- Excel in STEM fields\n- Research experience\n- Academic competition achievements\n- Strong mathematics and science background\n\n5. Supplemental Achievements\n- Demonstrate unique talents\n- Participate in national/international competitions\n- Engage in significant community service\n- Show intellectual curiosity\n\n6. Specialized Programs\n- Apply to specific schools within Johns Hopkins (Engineering, Arts/Sciences)\n- Consider direct medical programs\n- Highlight specialized academic interests\n\n7. Holistic Evaluation\n- JHU considers overall character\n- Demonstrate potential to contribute to university community\n- Show intellectual vitality\n\nCompetitive admissions require exceptional overall profile.",
